RIM to Sell 1 Million Blackberry Phones in Turkey, Hurriyet Says

-- B y   E r c a n   E r s o y
-- 
2011-05-06T05:54:16Z

-- http://www.bloomberg.com/news/2011-05-06/rim-to-sell-1-million-blackberry-phones-in-turkey-hurriyet-says.html
Research In Motion Ltd. (RIM) , maker of the
BlackBerry, plans to increase its smartphone sales in  Turkey  to
1 million units from 400,000 now,  Hurriyet  said, citing
Alexandra Zagury, the company’s country manager.  The company will invest more in Turkey to expand marketing,
Zagury said, according to the Istanbul-based newspaper. The
newspaper didn’t say when RIM plans to sell 1 million units.  To contact the reporter on this story:
Ercan Ersoy in Istanbul at 
 eersoy@bloomberg.net .  To contact the editor responsible for this story:
Benedikt Kammel at 
 bkammel@bloomberg.net . 